file=Cybersecurity/keyring/operational/commands/keyring-commands.md · tb=\| Trigger phrases \| Skill \| Shortcut \| · tb=\|---\|---\|---\| · tb=\| "provision," "onboard," "offboard," "deprovision," "role change," "joiner/mover/leaver" \| identity-lifecycle \| /keyring-jml \| · tb=\| "access review," "recertify," "who has access," "privilege creep," "orphan accounts" \| access-reviews \| /keyring-review \| · tb=\| "admin access," "root," "privileged," "break-glass," "just-in-time" \| privileged-access-management \| /keyring-pam \| · tb=\| "secrets," "API key," "rotate," "vault," "hardcoded credential," "leaked secret" \| secrets-governance \| /keyring-secrets \| · p:Precedence=1. **Leaver = deprovision ALL systems** (IdP + SaaS + shared + secrets) — the loudest gap; never partial.\n2. Any **grant/revoke/rotation** is executed by the operator/IdP/PAM/vault — keyring designs and recommends, never executes (the security-inversion).\n3. **Revoke-then-appeal** at reviews — unjustified access is removed by default.\n4. A **found/leaked secret** is treated as compromised → rotate (not just delete) → alert cortex.\n